The paper deals with a model of communication in a social network, which is a topic related to social networks and information retrieval (cs.SI). The problem of finding a subset of nodes that enable the fastest convergence rate to equilibrium is a problem in control and optimization (cs.SY). The use of expected first hitting times is a topic in probability and statistics (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the mixing theory of Markov chains, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
